accessrestrict.p: Series 1 and 3 are closed to research for 25 years from date of record creation.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Materials acquired through transfers from the Columbian College Alumni Association.

userestrict.head: Restrictions on Use
userestrict.p: Some material may be copyrighted or restricted. It is the patron's obligation to determine and satisfy copyright or other case restrictions when publishing or otherwise distributing materials found in the collections.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The Columbian College alumni association dates back to the 1850s. Columbian College of Arts and Science is the liberal arts college within the university. Today the Columbian College Alumni Association is a part of the General Alumni Association.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Materials in this collection include "Arts and Sciences," a newsletter for alumni of Columbian College of Arts and Sciences, photographs, "First 50 years of Columbian College" exhibit, materials relating to reunion weekends and homecoming. The collections covers the years 1965 to 1993.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into four series: Columbian College alumni association files; Newsletter; Alumni events; Photographs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series consists of materials relating to reunions, receptions, and events (including Phi Beta Kappa 50th anniversary, "phonathon," annual fund, poetry reading). The materials range in date from 1965-88.
